.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH ox-logs 1  "ox-logs " 
.SH NAME
ox\-logs \- View job logs
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBox\-logs\fR [\fB\-\-rule\fR] [\fB\-\-failed\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-follow\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-db\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIJOB_ID\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
View job logs
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-rule\fR \fI<RULE>\fR
Filter by rule name (show logs for all matching jobs)
.TP
\fB\-\-failed\fR
Show only failed jobs
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-follow\fR
Follow (tail \-f) the log for an active job
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output structured JSON
.TP
\fB\-\-db\fR \fI<DB>\fR [default: .oxymake/state.db]
Path to state.db
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIJOB_ID\fR]
Job ID to show logs for
